{"questionId":"9069388","questionHtml":"<p>Write an equation for the reaction between the acids to produce the electrophile, NO<sub>2</sub><sup>+</sup>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>HNO<sub>3</sub> + 2H<sub>2</sub>SO<sub>4</sub>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" class=\"wrs_chemistry\"><mo>⇌</mo></math> NO<sub>2</sub><sup>+</sup> + H<sub>3</sub>O<sup>+</sup> + 2HSO<sub>4</sub><sup>-</sup> ✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Accept “HNO<sub>3</sub> + H<sub>2</sub>SO<sub>4</sub>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" class=\"wrs_chemistry\"><mo>⇌</mo></math> NO<sub>2</sub><sup>+</sup> + H<sub>2</sub>O + HSO<sub>4</sub><sup>-</sup>”.</em></p>\n<p><em>Accept “HNO<sub>3</sub> + H<sub>2</sub>SO<sub>4</sub>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" class=\"wrs_chemistry\"><mo>⇌</mo></math> H<sub>2</sub>NO<sub>3</sub><sup>+</sup> + HSO<sub>4</sub><sup>-</sup>” <strong>AND</strong> “H<sub>2</sub>NO<sub>3</sub><sup>+</sup>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" class=\"wrs_chemistry\"><mo>⇌</mo></math> NO<sub>2</sub><sup>+</sup> + H<sub>2</sub>O”.</em></p>\n<p><em>Accept single arrows instead of equilibrium signs.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9069388","referenceCode":"22M.2.hl.TZ1.b(i)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Write an equation for the reaction between the acids to produce the electrophile, NO2+.","paper":"2","level":"hl","questionNumber":"b(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 20: Organic chemistry","20.1 Types of organic reactions","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 20: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}